1:
Give thanks to Yahweh, call on his name;
\q make known his deeds among the nations.
\q

2:
Sing to him, sing praises to him;
\q speak of all his marvelous deeds.
\q

4:
Seek Yahweh and his strength;
\q seek his presence continually.
\q

14:
He did not allow anyone to oppress them;
\q he rebuked kings for their sakes.
\q

16:
He called for a famine on the land;
\q he cut off the whole supply of bread.
\q

18:
His feet were bound by shackles;
\q on his neck was put an iron collar,
\q

20:
The king sent servants to release him;
\q the ruler of the people set him free.
\q

35:
The locusts ate up all of the vegetation in their land;
\q They ate up all the crops of the ground.
\q

37:
He brought the Israelites out with silver and gold;
\q none of his tribes stumbled on the way.
\q

41:
He split the rock, and waters gushed from it;
\q they flowed in the wilderness like a river.
\q

44:
He gave them the lands of the nations;
\q they took possession of the wealth of the peoples
\q
